--> Socket binds the IP and the port number
	port numbers are the unique number given to the ports/point-of-communication
	
--> Stream socket is a connection oriented which uses the TCP protocol
	Datagram socket is a connectionless which uses the UDP protocol
	
--> The set of API's:-
	Client Side:-
		socket()
		connect()
		send()
		  |
		recv()
		close()
	Server Side:-
		socket()
		bind()
		listen()
		accept()
		recv()
		  |
		send()
		recv()
		  |
		close()
	
--> socket()
	1. Parameter specifies protocol/address family
	2. Parameter specifies the socket type
	3. Parameter specifies the protocol
	
	
	
